Package io.artframework.annotations

Annotation Type OnEnable

  • @Retention(RUNTIME)
@Target(METHOD)
public @interface OnEnable
    Marks the given method as the enable method for an art module. The class must be annotated with the @ArtModule annotation for the method to be called.

    The enable method is called after bootstrapping has finished and the @OnLoad method was called. Use it to do the core tasks of your module, e.g. open a database connection, start services, and so on.

    The enable lifecycle method is called exactly once in the lifecycle of the module. Any reloading will happen with the @OnReload method.

    Any dependencies of this module will be enabled before this module. The lifecycle methods of this module will never be called if this module has missing dependencies.

    The annotated method can take any of the following parameters, but most not take any other parameters.

    • Scope - the scope of the module
